<paragraph base="F55666562" principles="yes" id="IFRS17_80"><paranum>80</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 17"/><data name="paranum" value="80"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS17_P0310">Applying <xref base="F59233782" href="IFRS17_41.dita#IFRS17_41" id="IFRS17_X0367">paragraphs 41 and 42</xref>, an entity shall disaggregate the amounts recognised in the statement(s) of profit or loss and other comprehensive income (hereafter referred to as the statement(s) of financial performance) into: </p><ol base="F55666564" type="lower-alpha" id="IFRS17_L0059"><li id="IFRS17_80_a"><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p base="F55666565" id="IFRS17_P0311">an insurance service result (<xref base="F59233783" href="IFRS17_g83-86.dita#IFRS17_g83-86/IFRS17_g83-86_TI" id="IFRS17_X0368">paragraphs 83&#x2013;86</xref>), comprising insurance revenue and insurance service expenses; and</p>       </li><li id="IFRS17_80_b"><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p base="F55666567" id="IFRS17_P0312">insurance finance income or expenses (<xref base="F59233784" href="IFRS17_g87-92.dita#IFRS17_g87-92/IFRS17_g87-92_TI" id="IFRS17_X0369">paragraphs 87&#x2013;92</xref>).</p>       </li></ol></body></paragraph>